    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-26T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="15"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d15">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.4731/132: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Sydney</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moffat</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sydney</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-26T15:00:00+10:00"
                            >September 26, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 26—5:14 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s September 23, 6 p.m. Proceeding to Canberra for week’s visit on
                    October 1st.</p>
                <p>The press here is no longer referring to the imminence of a trade treaty with the
                    United States. Neither Squire<note n="10" xml:id="d15fn10">E. C. Squire,
                        American Trade Commissioner at Sydney.</note> nor I know of any present plan
                    to send a special delegation to the United States to negotiate a reciprocal
                    trade agreement though it is still expected that Gullett will stop over in
                    Washington on his way home from Europe to explore the situation in greater
                    detail than did Lyons. Gullett’s trade discussions with continental countries
                    have to date been unproductive.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moffat</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
